==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Extempore
<hw>Ex*tem"po*re</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>ex</ets> out + <ets>tempus</ets>, <ets>temporis</ets>, time. See
<er>Temporal</er>.]</ety> <def>Without previous study or meditation;
without preparation; on the spur of the moment; suddenly;
extemporaneously; <as>as, to write or speak
<ex>extempore</ex></as>.</def> <au>Shak.</au> -- <def2><pos>a.</pos>
<def>Done or performed extempore.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Extempore</xex>
dissertation.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Addison.</au> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Extempore</xex>
poetry.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Dryden.</au></def2> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos>
<def>Speaking or writing done extempore.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<au>Bp. Fell.</au></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Extemporiness</ent>⟦br⟧
